name: facestream
readme_summary: FaceStream is a web application enabling real-time face swapping by utilizing a remote server and WebRTC.  It addresses performance limitations of running such applications locally on low-powered devices.  The application is deployed using Modal and optionally integrates a TURN server for improved cellular network compatibility.
key_features: Real-time face swapping web application
Uses WebRTC for remote server communication
Runs on a remote server for accessibility on low-powered devices
Leverages the Deep Live Cam model (non-commercial use only)
Uses Modal for deployment and hosting
Optional TURN server integration for cellular networks
primary_use_case: Real-time face swapping in a web browser without requiring a high-performance local machine

name: forge
readme_summary: Forge is an AI-powered terminal development environment offering advanced coding assistance, including code generation, debugging, testing, and documentation.  It integrates seamlessly with Unix tools and provides a secure, multi-agent architecture for complex development tasks.  Its natural language interface and fast performance enhance developer workflow.
key_features: Advanced AI coding assistant for writing, refactoring, optimizing, debugging, testing, documenting, and proposing architectural improvements
Lightning-fast performance with sub-50ms startup times
Seamless integration with existing Unix tools and workflows
Context-aware assistance understanding the development environment
Natural language interface for system operations
Enhanced security with optional restricted shell mode
Multi-agent architecture for collaborative problem-solving
Powered by Claude 3.7 Sonnet
primary_use_case: AI-enhanced terminal development environment for efficient coding assistance

name: Font-Awesome
description: The iconic SVG, font, and CSS toolkit
readme_summary: Font Awesome provides a vast library of icons available in various formats (.svg, .js, web and desktop fonts).  Version 6 follows Semantic Versioning with some exceptions noted for major releases.  Licensing covers icons, fonts, and code under CC BY 4.0, SIL OFL 1.1, and MIT licenses respectively.
key_features: Icon library and toolkit
Version 6 with LTS support for version 5
Semantic Versioning (with exceptions for major releases)
Web and desktop font files
.svg and .js files
CC BY 4.0, SIL OFL 1.1, and MIT Licenses
primary_use_case: Providing icons for designers, developers, and content creators

name: zentral
description: Zentral is a high-visibility platform for controlling Apple endpoints in enterprises. It brings great observability to IT and makes tracking & reporting compliance much less manual.
readme_summary: Zentral is an Event Hub designed to collect, process, and monitor system events, correlating them with an asset inventory.  It facilitates comprehensive event management and provides insights into system behavior through event-inventory linkage.  This allows for improved troubleshooting and proactive system maintenance.
key_features: Gather system events
Process system events
Monitor system events
Link events to inventory
primary_use_case: Event Hub for system events and inventory linking

name: postiz-app
description: üì® The ultimate social media scheduling tool, with a bunch of AI  ü§ñ
readme_summary: Postiz is an AI-powered social media scheduling tool that allows users to schedule posts, measure performance with analytics, and collaborate with team members.  It offers a range of AI features and has no functional difference between hosted and self-hosted versions.
key_features: Schedule social media posts
AI features for post creation and scheduling
Analytics for measuring post performance
Team collaboration features for post exchange and scheduling
No difference between hosted and self-hosted versions
primary_use_case: AI-powered social media scheduling and management tool

name: Cuda-120-Days-Challenge
description: A 120-day CUDA learning plan covering daily concepts, exercises, pitfalls, and references (including ‚ÄúProgramming Massively Parallel Processors‚Äù). Features six capstone projects to solidify GPU parallel programming, memory management, and performance optimization skills.
readme_summary: This repository provides a structured 120-day curriculum for mastering CUDA programming.  It includes daily lessons with exercises, debugging advice, and resource suggestions, culminating in six capstone projects to solidify skills in GPU parallel programming, memory management, and performance optimization. The curriculum covers topics such as GPU vs. CPU architecture, thread hierarchy, kernel launch and execution, and memory management.
key_features: 120-day CUDA learning plan
daily concepts, exercises, and debugging tips
six capstone projects
focus on GPU parallel programming, memory management, and performance optimization

name: readyset
description: Readyset is a MySQL and Postgres wire-compatible caching layer that sits in front of existing databases to speed up queries and horizontally scale read throughput. Under the hood, ReadySet caches the results of cached select statements and incrementally updates these results over time as the underlying data changes.
readme_summary: ReadySet is a database cache that enhances the speed and scalability of Postgres and MySQL databases.  It automatically handles cache invalidation and synchronization, working seamlessly with existing applications and tools.  This is achieved by leveraging the database's replication stream for efficient cache management.
key_features: Transparent database cache for Postgres & MySQL
Performance and scalability of an in-memory key-value store
Automatic cache invalidation
Synchronization of cached query results with the database using database replication stream
Wire-compatible with Postgres and MySQL
Can be used with existing ORMs or database clients
primary_use_case: Improving the performance and scalability of database reads by caching query results

name: pglite
description: Lightweight WASM Postgres with real-time, reactive bindings.
readme_summary: PGlite is a lightweight WASM build of Postgres, offering a TypeScript client library for running Postgres in various environments.  It supports both in-memory and persistent databases, utilizing IndexedDB for browsers and the file system for Node.js, Bun, and Deno.  Its small size and compatibility with numerous extensions make it suitable for building reactive and local-first applications.
key_features: WASM build of Postgres
TypeScript client library
Runs in browser, Node.js, Bun, and Deno
Supports many Postgres extensions, including pgvector
3mb gzipped
Ephemeral in-memory database support
Persistence to file system (Node/Bun/Deno) or IndexedDB (Browser)
No Linux virtual machine required
primary_use_case: Build reactive, realtime, local-first apps directly on Postgres

name: OsintIA_Tools
description: OsintIA_Tools.py is an automated tool for collecting and analyzing public information that combines OSINT techniques with artificial intelligence, providing detailed insights into cybersecurity, potential vulnerabilities, and best mitigation practices.
readme_summary: OsintIA_Tools.py automates OSINT analysis using various tools like Shodan, Nmap, and Amass.  It generates detailed HTML reports with AI-powered insights, including prioritized recommendations for mitigating identified risks.  The tool focuses on improving cybersecurity by identifying vulnerabilities and threats.
key_features: IP resolution using Shodan with dig and ping fallbacks
WHOIS lookup using Amass as a fallback
Port scanning using Nmap
Subdomain enumeration (tools not specified)
Metadata extraction using Metagoofil (supports doc, docx, zip)
HTML report generation with interactive index
AI-powered analysis using OpenAI API (interprets results and suggests actions)
Detailed report including summary of results from each tool, critical risks, and prioritized recommendations
Improved OpenAI API connection with retry system and strategic pauses
DNSEnum optimization using reliable DNS servers and adjusted timeout/threads
Enhanced report formatting with clear paragraphs and removal of ANSI codes
primary_use_case: Automated OSINT analysis for cybersecurity purposes, identifying potential vulnerabilities and threats

name: pangolin
description: Tunneled Mesh Reverse Proxy Server with Identity and Access Control and Dashboard UI
readme_summary: Pangolin is a self-hosted reverse proxy that creates secure tunnels via WireGuard, enabling access to private resources without port forwarding.  It features a centralized authentication system with access control rules and a user-friendly dashboard for management.  Deployment is simplified with Docker Compose and an installation script.
key_features: Reverse Proxy Through WireGuard Tunnel
Identity & Access Management
Simple Dashboard UI
Easy Deployment
Modular Design
primary_use_case: Securely expose private resources on distributed networks without opening ports, using a self-hosted tunneled reverse proxy server with access control.
